Description: Limestone ostracon: on recto and verso respectively five and three lines of an administrative text recording measurements of elements of a royal tomb, almost certainly that of Ramses VI, no. 9 in the Valley of the Kings.
Curator's comments: Completed (upper half) by O. Berlin B (unpublished). Bibliography: J. J. Černy, 'The Valley of the Kings' (Cairo, 1973), p. 5; S. Wimmer, 'Hieratische Paläographie der nicht-literarischen Ostraka der 19. und 20. Dynastie' (Agypten und Altes Testament 29) (Wiesbaden, 1996), pp. 36-7 (transcription of recto), 138 (facsimile).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136267) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136267)
Associated places: Named in inscription: Biban el-Muluk (Valley of the Kings - Thebes), Tomb of Ramses VI, no. 9
